# Go Logging

> References: `internal/logging/logging.go`, `internal/logging/ctx.go`

## How it Works

`logging.New(...)` wraps the slog handler with a `contextHandler`. When you call `logger.InfoContext(ctx, ...)`, the `contextHandler` automatically stamps any values stored in the context (`operation`, `request_id`, `client_ip`) onto every log record — no manual extraction needed.

**Always use `InfoContext`/`ErrorContext`/`WarnContext`/`DebugContext`, not `Info`/`Error`/etc.** Only the `Context` variants trigger the `contextHandler` stamp.

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Logger source | Context values |
|---|---|---|
| Middleware | — | Sets `request_id` and `client_ip` in ctx via `logging.WithRequestID`, `logging.WithClientIP` |
| Handler | `h.logger` field (injected at construction) | Sets `operation` in ctx via `logging.WithOperation(ctx, "MethodName")` |
| Service | `s.logger` field (injected at construction) | Reads ctx attrs automatically via `contextHandler` |
| Repository | `slog.Default()` in `runInTx` only (infra-level fallback) | — |

## Handler Pattern

```go
func (h *HTTPHandler) CreateDevice(ctx context.Context, req ...) (...) {
    // Store operation in ctx — contextHandler stamps it on every record below
    ctx = logging.WithOperation(ctx, "CreateDevice")
    // Enrich the logger with call-specific attrs
    logger := h.logger.With(slog.String(AttrKeyDeviceName, req.Body.Name))

    device, rawKey, err := h.service.CreateDevice(ctx, req.Body.Name)
    if err != nil {
        switch {
        case errors.Is(err, ErrDuplicateDeviceName):
            logger.WarnContext(ctx, "duplicate device name")
            return httpapi.CreateDevice409JSONResponse(...), nil
        default:
            logger.ErrorContext(ctx, "failed to create device", slog.Any(AttrKeyError, err))
            return httpapi.CreateDevice500JSONResponse(...), nil
        }
    }

    logger.InfoContext(ctx, "device created", slog.Int64(AttrKeyDeviceID, device.ID.Int64()))
    return httpapi.CreateDevice201JSONResponse(...), nil
}
```

**Rules:**
- `ctx = logging.WithOperation(ctx, "MethodName")` at the top of every handler — only handlers set `operation`
- `h.logger.With(...)` for call-specific enrichment; reassign to `logger`
- `Warn` for 4xx (client errors); `Error` for 5xx (server errors)
- Do NOT log HTTP status codes — `slog-chi` middleware owns request/response logging

## Service Pattern

```go
func (s *Service) CreateDevice(ctx context.Context, name string) (*Device, string, error) {
    // s.logger already carries component="device" from construction
    // ctx carries operation, request_id, client_ip — stamped automatically by contextHandler

    device, err := s.repo.CreateDevice(ctx, &CreateDeviceParams{Name: name})
    if err != nil {
        s.logger.ErrorContext(ctx, "failed to create device", slog.Any(AttrKeyError, err))
        return nil, "", err
    }
    s.logger.InfoContext(ctx, "device created", slog.Int64(AttrKeyDeviceID, device.ID.Int64()))
    return device, rawKey, nil
}
```

**Rules:**
- Use `s.logger` directly — do not extract a logger from context
- Never call `logging.WithOperation` — operation is set by the handler
- Add per-call attrs inline; only use `s.logger.With(...)` if you need to pass attrs into nested sub-service calls

## Message & Key Conventions

- **Static messages only** — no `fmt.Sprintf`; put dynamic data in slog attributes
- Use domain-defined key constants (`AttrKeyDeviceID`, `AttrKeyError`, …), not raw string literals
- All key values must be `snake_case`
- Always `slog.Any(AttrKeyError, err)` — never `slog.String(..., err.Error())`. Using `Any` preserves the error value so structured handlers (JSON, custom) can inspect its type and any `LogValuer` fields; `String` collapses it to a plain string.
- Avoid reserved keys: `time`, `level`, `msg`, `source`

## Log Levels

- `Debug` — intermediate steps (`"assigning address"`)
- `Info` — successful outcomes (`"device created"`)
- `Warn` — expected/client errors (`"device not found"`, `"invalid IP format"`)
- `Error` — unexpected failures (`"database error fetching device"`)

## Bootstrap

```go
logger := logging.New(logging.Options{
    Level:  logging.ParseLevel(conf.LogLevel),  // LOG_LEVEL env var
    Format: conf.LogFormat,                      // LOG_FORMAT: "json" or tint
    Color:  conf.LogColor,                       // LOG_COLOR env var
})
slog.SetDefault(logger) // Required: infra code (e.g. runInTx) falls back to slog.Default()
// Domain packages (services, handlers) receive *slog.Logger via constructor — do not call slog.Default()
```
